Solution

Formatting of the P&L table
Let's insert a new row at the top of the table to display key information. On the left, we'll note that the figures are in thousands (000s) and denominated in USD. On the right, we'll indicate that these numbers pertain to the year 2024.
To better emphasize the header row, I will apply bold formatting and add a bottom border.
Similarly, we can enhance the readability of our table by highlighting the subtotal and total rows. For the subtotal rows, I will use bold formatting and add a top border.
Net income, as the total of the table, will be emphasized with distinct formatting. I'll use a top border and a thick bottom border to highlight it more effectively.
Our P&L is nearly complete. The last detail to add is a thousand separator for clearer financial figures. To do this, I'll select all financial figures, right-click, and choose 'Format Cells.' Within the 'Numbers' category, we'll select 'Use 1000 Separator (,)'
